# Theming for new pages

When adding **any new route page or shared UI component**, use the app's theme variables so the accessibility themes (Default, High contrast, Alternative) apply correctly.

- Use `bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `text-muted`, `bg-surface`, `border-border`, `bg-primary text-primary-foreground`, `hover:bg-[var(--primary-hover)]`, and focus rings with `focus:ring-[var(--primary)]`. Do **not** use hardcoded zinc/gray classes for layout, text, cards, or buttons.
- See **docs/THEMING.md** for the full token list and checklist for new pages.
